==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: slit-shell
<hw>slit"-shell`</hw> <pr>(sl⟦icr⟧t"sh⟦ecr⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any species of <gen>Pleurotomaria</gen>, a genus
of beautiful, pearly, spiral gastropod shells having a deep slit in the
outer lip. Many fossil species are known, and a few living ones are
found in deep water in tropical seas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>slitter</ent>⟦br⟧
